It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



Waste-specific emissions from lignite spoil leachate. Short- and long-term emissions to groundwater from rainwater infiltration leaching. Leaching by lateral groundwater flow not included.
category: E:Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities/38:Waste collection, treatment and disposal activities; materials recovery/382:Waste treatment and disposal/3822:Treatment and disposal of hazardous waste

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Average coal tailings composition from literature references. Transfer coefficients from prospective model, specific to coal tailings.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data represents a worldwide average. Generic water infiltration rate according to weighted mean of major sites of coal tailings production in the world.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Mechanically stable and revegetated coal tailings impoundment
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: missing values adopted by proxy from lignite spoil
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Disposal model based on observed leachate concentrations in literature. Extrapolated to 60'000 years heeding chemical characteristics. Initial tailings composition from various literature sources.
